Global Diamond and Gemstone Market Insights
Diamond and Gemstone Market size was valued at USD 80 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 110 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Diamond and Gemstone Market Overview
The global diamond and gemstone market is valued at approximately USD 87.77 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow at a steady pace. With increasing demand for luxury jewelry, fine cuts, and precious stones across global markets, the industry is witnessing positive growth. Factors such as rising disposable income, increasing awareness of ethical sourcing, and growing consumer interest in sustainable diamonds and gemstones are expected to fuel market expansion. Asia Pacific and North America are key regions contributing to the growth, owing to the high demand for both investment-grade diamonds and designer jewelry. However, challenges such as economic volatility, ethical concerns, and fluctuating raw material prices may hinder market progress in certain segments.

